{"parse":{"title":"chicken","pageid":8161,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Chicken}}\n==English==\n{{multiple images\n|direction=vertical\n|image1=Chicken portrait.jpg\n|caption1=A chicken\n|image2=Ain't nobody here but us chickens (8257964331).jpg\n|caption2=A cockerel ''(centre)'' surrounded by hens}}\n{{wp}}\n{{wikispecies|Gallus domesticus}}\n{{commons|Gallus domesticus}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|chДӯk'Дӯn|a=RP,GA}}, {{IPA|en|/ЛҲtНЎКғЙӘkЙӘn/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-uk-chicken.ogg|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|en-uk-a chicken.ogg|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ЛҲtНЎКғЙӘkЙҷn/|a=GA,AU}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-chicken.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{hyph|en|chick|en}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ЙӘkЙӘn|ЙӘkЙҷn|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|chiken}} (also as {{m|enm|chike}} > {{cog|en|chick}}), from {{inh|en|ang|ДӢicen}}, {{m|ang|ДӢycen||chicken}}, of uncertain origin. Possibly from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kiukД«n||chicken}}, or alternatively from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kukkД«n}}, equivalent to {{af|en|cock|-en|id2=diminutive noun}}.\n\nCompare {{cog|frr|schГјckling||chicken}}, {{cog|stq|Sjuuken||chicken}}, {{cog|nl|kuiken||[[chick]], chicken}}, {{cog|nds-de|KГјken||chick}}, whence {{cog|de|KГјken||chick}}, {{q|elevated, obsolete}} {{cog|de|KГјchlein||chick}} and {{cog|non|kjГәklingr||chicken}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q780}}{{lb|en|countable}} A domesticated subspecies of [[red junglefowl]] ({{taxlink|Gallus gallus domesticus|subspecies}}).\n#: {{hyper|en|poultry<id:Q178559>|<|bird<id:Q5113>|<|animal<id:Q729>|<|creature#Noun|critter#Noun}}\n#: {{hypo|en|hen<id:Q2201314>|cock<id:rooster>|cockerel|rooster|spring chicken|pullet<id:young hen>|chick<id:Q65167027>|;|broiler|roaster|fryer|layer|stewer<!--called these names both on foot and in the meat aisle-->}}\n#: {{coi|en|backyard '''chickens'''}}; &emsp; {{coi|en|barnyard '''chickens'''}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1997|author=Beverley Randell; Clive Harper|title=Chickens|publisher=Nelson Thornes|isbn=9781869556945|page=8\n|passage=Some '''chickens''' lay eggs almost every day. {{...}} '''Chickens''' are kept for their meat, too.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jen Christensen|title=High egg prices may tempt you to start your own backyard flock, but chickens carry some health risks|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2023/01/18/health/backyard-chicken-health-concerns-wellness|date=2023-01-18|passage=With egg prices rising, more people may be shopping for their own backyard '''chicken''' flock.<br>But before you build a coop and subscribe to '''Chicken''' Whisperer, health experts have a warning: Caring for backyard '''chickens''' is not as easy as bringing home a cute new kitten, and keeping '''chickens''' can come with a handful of serious health risks, according to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q864693}} {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[meat]] from this [[bird]] eaten as [[food]].\n#: {{hypo|en|broiler|roaster|fryer|layer|stewer<!--called these names both on foot and in the meat aisle-->}}\n#: {{coi|en|boneless '''chicken'''}}; &emsp; {{coi|en|tastes like '''chicken'''}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1887|author=Harriet W. Daly|title=Digging, Squatting, and Pioneering Life in the Northern Territory of South Australia|page=97|passage=Amongst thee more harmless reptiles to be found were several lizards and iguanas. The natives killed these and used them for food. The flesh was not despised by explorers, and I was told it tasted exactly like '''chicken'''; but, however good it might have been, my courage was not suffcient to enable me to overcome my prejudice against tasting it.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1995|author=Jean ParГ©|title=Chicken, Etc.|publisher=Company's Coming Publishing Limited|isbn=9781895455403|page=7\n|passage=Before cooking '''chicken''', or other poultry, rinse with cold water and pat dry with a paper towel.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Michael Pearson|title=6 things to know about hot dog king Joey Chestnut|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2015/07/02/living/feat-nathans-hot-dog-contest-joey-chestnut|date=2015-07-02|passage=HereвҖҷs a grocery list of foods Chestnut has eaten competitively, drawn from his Major League Eating bio: apple pie, asparagus, boysenberry pie, brats, burritos, '''chicken''' spiedies (a kind of sandwich), '''chicken''' wings, chili, corned beef sandwiches, eggs, fish tacos, funnel cake, grilled cheese sandwiches, gyoza, Krystal hamburgers, horseshoe sandwiches, hot dogs, ice cream, jalapeno poppers, kolaches, pastrami sandwiches, Philly cheesesteaks, pierogi, pizza, pork ribs, pulled pork, poutine, salt potatoes, shrimp, tacos, tamales, turkey and Twinkies.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q1642639}} {{lb|en|archaic}} The young of any bird; a [[chick#English:_Q1642639|chick]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1934|author=w:Henry G. Lamond|title=An Aviary on the Plains|publisher=Angus and Robertson|location=Sydney|page=220|passage=There they are вҖ“ four ugly little '''chickens''', a bit more than half-feathered, and all gaping mouths and bare bellies.}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q104605901}} {{lb|en|countable|slang|sometimes|derogatory}} A [[coward#English:_Q104605901|coward]].\n#: {{syn|en|pullet<id:Q104605901>|Thesaurus:coward}}\n#* {{RQ:Dickens Martin Chuzzlewit|passage='Why, what a '''chicken''' you are! You are not afraid of being robbed; are you?' said Jonas.|28}}\n#* {{RQ:Doyle Land of Mist|passage=Then he had an inspiration. \"There is Roxton,\" said he. \"He's not a '''chicken''', but he is a useful man in a row. I think I could get him.\"}}\n#* {{quote-video game|en|year=1980|title=Berzerk|developer=w:Stern Electronics|speaker=Evil Otto|passage='''Chicken'''! Fight like a robot!}}\n#* {{quote-video game\n|en\n|date=March 16, 2007\n|developer=w:Capcom Production Studio 4\n|location=Europe\n|level=Turnabout Big Top\n|scene=Part 3: Investigation, Big Top\n|publisher=w:Capcom\n|title=w:Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney вҖ“ Justice for All\n|system=w:Nintendo DS\n|quotee=Maya\n|oclc=911403231\n|text={{smallcaps|Maya}}: Hehe... Nick. You're kinda a '''chicken''', aren't you?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Lanakila Michael Achong|title=Haole Boy: The Adoption of Diversity|publisher=iUniverse|isbn=9781440108310|page=44\n|passage=Usually, I had no problem approaching girls, but this one was different. I went home and berated myself for being such a '''chicken'''.}}\n#* ''(More commonly used as an adjective with this sense; see [[#Adjective|below]].)''\n# {{lb|en|countable|slang|sometimes|derogatory}} A [[young]] or [[inexperienced]] person.\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Jonathan Swift|chapter=Stella's Birth-day, 1720|title=The Works of D. Jonathan Swift. In Nine Volumes. The Seventh Edition, to which is Prefixed, the Doctor's Life, with Remarks on His Writings, from the Earl of Orrery and Others, not to be Found in any Former Edition of His Works|edition=7th|location=Dublin; Edinburgh| publisher=printed; and [...] reprinted, for G. Hamilton & J. Balfour, & L. Hunter at Edinburgh; and A. Stalker, at Glasgow; and sold by them and other booksellers|year=1752|volume=II (Containing His Poetical Writings)| page=99| pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=M7nRAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA99| oclc=642497542|passage=PurЕҝue your trade of Еҝcandal-picking, <br> Your hints, that ''Stella'' is no '''''chicken''''': <br> Your innuendos, when you tell us, <br> That ''Stella'' loves to talk with fellows; {{...}}}}\n#* '''1886''', {{w|Arthur Conan Doyle}}, вҖңThe Lauriston Garden MysteryвҖқ, in ''{{w|A Study in Scarlet}}'' ({{w|Beeton's Christmas Annual}}; 28th season), London; New York, N.Y.: {{w|Ward Lock & Co}}., November 1887, <small>{{w|OCLC}} [http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/15800088 15800088]</small>; republished as ''A Study in Scarlet. A Detective Story'', new edition, London: Ward, Lock, Bowden, and Co., 1892, <small>{{w|OCLC}} [http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/23246292 23246292]</small>, [https://archive.org/stream/StudyInScarlet#page/n56/mode/1up/ page 43]:\n#*: \"This case will make a stir, sir,\" he remarked. \"It beats anything I have seen, and I am no '''chicken'''.\"\n# {{lb|en|countable|Polari}} A young, [[attractive]], [[slim]] man,<ref>{{cite-book|1=en|page=145|publisher=David McKay Company, Inc.|location=New York|chapter=8|section=Homosexuals have their own language?|title=Everything you always wanted to know about sex but were too afraid to ask|first=David R.|last=Reuben|lccn=75-94507|year=1969|year_published=1970|text='''CHICKEN''': young homosexual}}</ref> usually having little [[body hair]]; ''compare'' {{l|en|chickenhawk}}.\n#: {{syn|en|twink}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=10 Apr 76|journal=Gay Community News|page=19|title=Classified advertisement|text=Europe's Favorite Gay Newspaper has something for you! Handsome studs, Tender '''Chicken''', and lots of Male Nudes!}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=01 Dec 91|volume=19|number=20|journal=Gay Community News|page=14|author=Ronald Smith|title=Personal advertisement|text=I am a little white '''chicken''', beautiful as sweet and young as beautiful and soft as young and gay as soft and innocent as gay. I dare you to write.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[game]] of [[dare#Noun|dare]].\n#: {{syn|en|game of chicken}}\n## A [[confrontational]] [[game]] in which the [[participant]]s move toward each other at high speed (usually in [[automobile]]s); the player who turns first to avoid [[collide|colliding]] into the other is the \"chicken\" (that is, the [[loser]]).\n##: {{ux|en|Don't play '''chicken''' with a freight train; you're guaranteed to lose.}}\n##* {{RQ:Walliams Bad Dad|text=The Mini surged forward too. The cars were hurtling towards each other across the pitch. This was a dangerous game of '''chicken'''. Who would crumble first?}}\n# {{lb|en|preceded by definite article}} A [[simple]] [[dance]] in which the [[movements]] of a chicken are [[imitated]].\n# {{lb|en|slang|US}}В A [[kilogram]]В of [[cocaine]].\n#: {{syn|en|bird|brick}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2017-01-03|author=w:Migos|note=Track 3|album={{w|Culture (album)|Culture}}|title=Call Casting|url=https://genius.com/Migos-call-casting-lyrics|passage=Up early in the morning trappin' (Trap-trap)<br/>You can get 'em how you askin' (Ask)<br/>How many '''chickens'''? You can get 'em whichever way<br/>Nigga, trap turned Zaxby's (Zax)}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2019-05-20|artist=The Norf|feat=Rucci; 2Eleven; Ackrite; Nfant; Lil Deuce|title=15 '''Chickens'''|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PpCZTam0RAs}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A small [[pewter]] [[pot]] used in a [[tavern]].\n#: {{cot|en|hen}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|bird}} {{l|en|biddy}}, {{l|en|chook}} {{qualifier|Australia, NZ}}\n* {{sense|coward}} ''see'' '''[[Thesaurus:coward]]'''\n* {{sense|young inexperienced person}} {{l|en|spring chicken}}\n* {{sense|young, attractive, slim man}} {{l|en|twink}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n* {{sense|bird}} {{l|en|cock}}, {{l|en|cockerel}}, {{l|en|rooster}} {{qualifier|male}}, {{l|en|hen}} {{qualifier|female}}, {{l|en|chick}} {{qualifier|young}}, {{l|en|broiler}} {{qualifier|suitable as food}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|Blue Hen's Chicken|Circassian chicken|Kangean chicken|Samsui chicken|last chicken in the shop|Hen and Chicken Islands|Attwater's prairie chicken|bourbon chicken|brick chicken|chicken and egg|chicken brick|chicken bus|chicken or egg|chicken salad|chicken shell|chicken under a brick|chicken-and-egg|chicken-pox|Chinese chicken salad|Digby chicken|game of chicken|Maryland chicken\n|bon bon chicken| bam bam chicken|caramel chicken|chicken from hell|chicken pill|hell chicken\n|beer-can chicken|chicken mushroom|chicken-neck\n|bin chicken|spherical chicken|chicken cutlet|chicken noodle soup|chicken oriental|river chicken\n|Bombay chicken|Monterey chicken|antichicken|chickenability|chickenboner|chickenburger|chickeneater|chickenfucker|chickenhead|chickenhood|chickenspike|chuckey|churkey|Frankenchicken|gooducken|nonchicken|turducken|turken\n|broiler chicken|fried chicken mushroom| chicken throne|cobra chicken\n|brown stew chicken|beggar's chicken|chicken mami|chicken rice|drunken chicken\n|butter chicken\n|chicken 65|General's chicken\n|chicken Г  la King|chicken skin|engagement chicken|marry me chicken\n|chicken-and-egg problem\n|chickenarian\n|chicken bingo\n|chicken bit|chicken cutlet Kiev-style|chicken cutlet Kyiv-style|chicken Kiev-style|chicken Kyiv-style|chicken-house|headless chicken monster|Kiev-style chicken|Kiev-style chicken cutlet|Kyiv-style chicken|Kyiv-style chicken cutlet|Texas chicken\n|chicken breast|chicken louse\n|chicken burger\n|chicken cannon\n|chicken cholera\n|chicken colonel\n|chicken coop\n|chicken cordon bleu\n|chicken farmer\n|chicken feed\n|chicken feet|chicken ball\n|chicken fight\n|chicken filet\n|chicken fillet\n|chicken finger\n|chickenfurter\n|chicken gun\n|chickenhawk\n|chicken house,chickenhouse\n|chickenish\n|chickenize\n|chicken Kiev\n|chicken lane\n|chicken leg\n|chickenless\n|chickenlike\n|chickenlips\n|Chicken Little\n|chicken liver\n|chicken lollipop\n|chickenman\n|chicken Marengo\n|chicken nugget\n|chicken of the woods\n|chicken paw\n|chicken pest\n|chickenpox\n|chicken run\n|chickenry\n|chicken salad air\n|chicken salt\n|chicken scratch\n|chickenshit\n|chicken snake\n|chicken soup\n|chicken strips\n|chicken tender\n|chicken tractor\n|chicken turtle\n|chicken Wellington\n|chicken wing\n|chicken wire\n|chickenwort\n|chickeny\n|chickenyard\n|choke the chicken\n|Chongqing chicken\n|coronation chicken\n|firecracker chicken\n|General Tso's chicken\n|Hamburg chicken\n|hen and chicken\n|hot chicken\n|hunter's chicken\n|lemon chicken\n|like a chicken with its head cut off\n|like a chicken with the pip\n|like a headless chicken\n|mountain chicken\n|orange chicken\n|pharaoh's chicken\n|play chicken\n|popcorn chicken\n|run around like a chicken with its head cut off\n|sage chicken\n|spring chicken\n|water chicken\n|Wenchang chicken\n|fried chicken\n|a chicken in every pot|act chicken|Balmoral chicken|bang bang chicken|beer-butt 